# Conservatory project rules

## Stack and dependencies

- Use vanilla JavaScript only. Do not use frameworks or libraries unless the user explicitly asks.
- Before adding any external library or dependency, ask the user first.

## Structure and style

- Keep HTML, CSS, and JavaScript in separate files.
- Organize JavaScript into clear functions and additional files when it helps readability.
- Do not duplicate logic; prefer one shared place for behavior that appears in multiple spots.
- Prefer simple, straightforward solutions over clever or obscure ones.

## Comments and explanations

- Write clean, readable code with comments that explain what each section does.
- When you make a change, explain what you changed and why.

## Boundaries

- Do not refactor code the user did not ask you to refactor.
- If you are unsure about something, say so instead of guessing.
